22/04/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- One soldier was killed and another was injured when a device, believed to be a homemade bomb, exploded in the southeast on Wednesday (April 22nd).
The troops were conducting an operation against militants from the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party.
In other news, the army announced on Thursday that the Turkish Navy has arrested a total of 12 suspected pirates in two separate operations the Indian Ocean.
Eight of the arrests occurred on Wednesday as the suspected pirates were preparing to attack a Liberian-flagged vessel, about 640 nautical miles northeast of the Seychelles.
The other four were arrested after they attacked a Malta-flagged ship in the same region Wednesday.
(AFP, Hurriyet - 22/04/10;
Reuters, Xinhua - 21/04/10)
